ed from the actual anomaly period!\n\nThis is a classic case of **missing server spans** during the fault period. The trace_analysis_tool shows:\n- HTTP 500 errors in all frontend pods (65-82 occurrences each)\n- A critical 71x latency increase in `checkoutservice` calling `hipstershop.CartService/GetCart`\n- But when I search for actual traces during the anomaly period, I only get traces from hours earlier\n\nThis indicates that during the anomaly period (23:10-23:32), the cartservice was not responding at all - likely because the service crashed or became completely unavailable. The checkoutservice client calls were timing out after waiting much longer than normal (hence the 71x latency increase), and this cascaded up to cause HTTP 500 errors in the frontend.\n\nThe fact that I can find normal cartservice traces from 15:00 (3 PM) but none from 23:10-23:32 (11 PM) strongly suggests the cartservice pods crashed or were terminated around the time the anomaly started.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"error_ratio\", \"rrt_max\", \"checkoutservice->cartservice\", \"http_status_code_500\"],\n  \"affected_components\": [\"cartservice\", \"checkoutservice\", \"frontend\"],\n  \"missing_traces\": [\"cartservice server spans during 2025-06-17 23:10:08 to 2025-06-17 23:32:08\"],\n  \"trace_summary\": \"HTTP 500 errors in frontend with 71x latency increase in checkoutservice->cartservice calls. Raw traces show normal operations at 15:00 but NO traces during the actual anomaly period (23:10-23:32), indicating cartservice crashed and became completely unresponsive.\",\n  \"next_verification\": {\n    \"action\": \"check_pod_status_at_timestamp\",\n    \"reason\": \"Complete absence of cartservice server spans during anomaly period suggests pod crash or termination\",\n    \"suggested_metrics\": [\"pod_processes\", \"pod_restart_count\", \"memory_usage\"],\n    \"suggested_log_keywords\": [\"cartservice\", \"OOMKilled\", \"exit\", \"crash\", \"terminated\"],\n    \"cr